ood requirements include those that cannot be considered chronically undernourished, but are likely being conditioned in their economic activity by insufficient food. According to the FAO, this is a broader measure of food adequacy in the population.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "ad79a942-0d8a-4e44-a646-02f98486e084": {"__data__": {"id_": "ad79a942-0d8a-4e44-a646-02f98486e084", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/grey-literature/women-environmental-decision-making-case-studies-ecuador-liberia-and", "Author": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Publisher": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Women in environmental decision making : case studies in Ecuador, Liberia, and the Philippines", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/grey-literature/women-environmental-decision-making-case-studies-ecuador-liberia-and", "Author": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Publisher": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "456ebe854fb18fbabe722c4eba75143fe1f98347542a7be0f8b7c7daab7f0e52"}, "2": {"node_id": "6b0f82b7-fd60-4f00-a03c-deb16a401aca", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/grey-literature/women-environmental-decision-making-case-studies-ecuador-liberia-and", "Author": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Publisher": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "bf2f3bb3e24a6d898ffbae41ee2ef54b724d0b645610f35e8ee4611ce74c22fb"}}, "hash": "c67020c048d80137ba4afcf4f36668d42645c5806ffde204cac68a3d2d91867f", "text": "According to the FAO, this is a broader measure 